Around ten-thousand people in the 33rd Annual Ghandi Walk in Lenasia, south of Johannesburg on Sunday. He was accompanied by the US Civil Rights Activist Reverend Jesse Jackson. The 12 kilometre fund raising walk was organised by the Ghandi Walk Committee to promote nation building and good health.  The proceeds of the walk will go to some community organisations working with people with disability and the elderly. Ntebo Mokobo has more… --SABC--